  "texts": [
    "Thus we imagine that the return can be any vector of the form µ + δ, where |δ i | ≤ ρ i.",
    "For example µ i = -0.0010 and ρ i = 0.0005 means that the mean return for asset i lies in the range [-15, -5] bps.",
    "We define the worst-case mean portfolio return as the minimum possible mean portfolio return consistent with the given ranges of asset return means:",
    "We can think of this as an adversarial game.",
    "The portfolio manager (PM) chooses the portfolio w, and an adversary then chooses the worst mean return consistent with the given uncertainty intervals."
  ],
